# Structure & naming

## Files & structure
- **One component per file.** Secondary render helpers → co-located `<Name>.helpers.tsx`.
- **Types** in co-located `<Name>.types.ts` or `frontend/src/types/` — avoid exported types
  inside `.tsx`.
- **Reusable pure functions** → `frontend/src/utils/`; **hooks** → `frontend/src/hooks/`.
- **Marketing pages** → `frontend/src/pages/marketing/`; other pages (e.g. legal) under `pages/`.
- **Routes:** central `frontend/src/config/routes.ts` (`ROUTES.*`) is the source of truth —
  keep `App.tsx` and nav links in sync with it; do not scatter path strings.

## Naming
- `PascalCase` components/types; `camelCase` variables/functions; `SCREAMING_SNAKE_CASE` consts.
- Booleans: `is/has/can/should`. Handlers: `handle*`; callback props: `on*`.
- Meaningful names — no `data`, `tmp`, `res`, `obj`.

## Safety & rendering
- **Null-safety:** coalesce optionals before string/array ops (`(value ?? '').trim()`).
- **No floating promises:** `await`, `void`, or `.catch()` in statement position.
- Extract loading/error/data branches into named `renderX()` helpers instead of deep ternaries.
- Respect Rules of Hooks.
